<section class="text-content p-3 m-3">
  <div class="container-md p-3 m-3">
    <p class="lead">Everything in a React application is a component. React lets you define components as classes or functions, but most of our components will be function components.</p>
    <p>A function component (also known as a functional component) is just a function that returns code stored inside a div.</p>
    <p class="lead">Class components, on the other hand, are used whenever we need to add state to a component. This component isn't a function. Instead, it's a custom class that extends the base functionality of a Component class that React provides.</p>
  </div>
</section>

